This paper deals with the effects of image compression techniques on adversarial examples, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) applications. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the security risks posed by adversarial attacks, which falls under the scope of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of pre-processing mechanisms to remove adversarial noise is related to the field of cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the comparison of different compression techniques involves the use of metrics and optimization algorithms, which are relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper proposes a new method for reducing adversarial noise using JPEG2000 compression, which is a topic of interest in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
